    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>Volga Germans, also known as Russian Germans, arrived in Northern Colorado around 1900.
        They initially worked as migrant workers on sugar beet farm. Many later settled permanently
        in the region. The Volga Germans of Milliken, Colorado, formed the German Congregational
        Church in 1918. The first minister for the Church was Rev. F. Schlitzkus. The church joined
        with the United Church of Christ at some point after 1957, and may have gone by the name of
        First Congregational (Deutsche) by that time. The church closed in 1977.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>This collection contains two registers that contain vital records for the members of the
        German Congregational Church in Milliken, Colorado. The first register contains membership
        information, baptismal records, marriage records, and confirmation records. The second
        register contains information related to the Sunday school.</p>
    </scopecontent>
